{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn about how to set up your project with the new authentication flow changes."}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/0210AuthFlowChange","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit"]]},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"ATProtoKit"}],"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","title":"0.21 to 0.26 Authentication Flow Migration"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/atprotokit\/0210authflowchange"]}],"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With the release of 0.26.0 comes a new migration flow for ATProtoKit developers. This change is fairly small, but this article will still cover what to expect in order to clear any confusion."}]},{"text":"Authentication Flow","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Authentication-Flow"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Previously, when you wanted to authenticate to an AT Protocol service, you used an initializer from ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":", which contained the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"handle"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"password","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" parameters. Then, you would use ATProtocolConfiguration.authenticate(authenticationFactorToken:) and passed the instance to the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoKit","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration(handle: example.bsky.social, password: hunter2)","","Task {","    do {","        \/\/ You can put it in here…","        try await config.authenticate()","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Or here…","        try await config.authenticate()","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"With version 0.26, this has been changed slightly:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration()","","Task {","    do {","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Enter the handle and password in here.","        try await config.authenticate(","            handle: example.bsky.social,","            password: hunter2","        )","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Here are the changes being made:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":"’s initializer no longer takes the "},{"code":"handle","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"code":"password","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" parameters: now, ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" is responsible."}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This is the only external change. However, more has been made internally:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSession","type":"reference"},{"text":" is no longer stored inside of ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":": now, a new "},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" named "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSessionRegistry"},{"type":"text","text":" holds all instances of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"struct"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UUID"},{"type":"text","text":" value has been added to the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":". This value is linked to all objects that are related to the session. This is part of the new initializer for "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":", named ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":" now closely follows "},{"code":"SessionConfiguration","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". In fact, the following methods are no longer stored in the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"text":", but have moved to default implementations of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/getSession()"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/refreshSession()","type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/deleteSession()","type":"reference"}]}]}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A new "},{"code":"protocol","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", named "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol"},{"text":", will now manage the management of the password, access token, and refresh token. An ","type":"text"},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", named "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain"},{"text":" is available for applications running on Apple’s platforms.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"anchor":"SessionConfiguration","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"`SessionConfiguration`"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As mentioned previously, "},{"code":"SessionConfiguration","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" now has default configurations for each of the required methods. It is also "},{"code":"Sendable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and requires a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"text":" to conform to it. The default implementation assumes you’re using an App Password to authenticate by default, but you’re able to create new implementations for your own conforming ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Furthermore, the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)-272a8"},{"text":" method handles Two-Factor Authentication, but the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"text":" can also handle OAuth. This is thanks to a ","type":"text"},{"code":"AsyncStream","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"-related properties, named ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeContinuation","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeStream","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Auto-managing the Keychain","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Auto-managing-the-Keychain"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As mentioned earlier, a new "},{"code":"protocol","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" have been made: ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain"},{"type":"text","text":" respectively. This manages the keychain items for the password and refresh token, as well as storing the access token in-memory."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The access token is being stored in-memory due to how frequently the token expires.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" conforms to ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol"},{"text":" and is the default object used for Apple platforms. It’s also the default object used when initializing with ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":". However, you’re free to create your own implementation if it doesn’t suit your needs."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"At this time, Linux and Windows developers will need to implement their own "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"text":" to achieve the same effect. However, default ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"text":"s for those platforms will be created at a later date.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside","style":"note"}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"article","references":{"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/UserSession":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSession","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","title":"UserSession","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UserSession","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"UserSession","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Represents an authenticated user session within the AT Protocol.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/atprotokit\/usersession"},"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/ATProtocolConfiguration/init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)":{"title":"init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Initializes a new instance of ","type":"text"},{"code":"ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic","fr